The term may also refer to the physical or electronic object containing such a work. 
Modern books are typically printed in a codex format, 
composed of many pages bound together and protected by a cover. 
Before the wide adoption of the modern printing press, 
codices were used to create handwritten manuscripts. 
Older writing media include scrolls and clay tablets.

Books are sometimes contrasted with periodical literature, 
such as newspapers or magazines, 
for which new editions are published according to a regular schedule